https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-palindrome/description/

QUESTION:
Input: s = "abccccdd"
Output: 7
SOLUTION:
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(1)
1)Create a hashset
2)if set does not contain then add the character to set
3)else if it contains then increase the count and remove the character from set.
4) return if set has no values then count else count+1

CODE:
class Solution {
    public int longestPalindrome(String s) {
        if(s.length()==0 || s==null)return 0;
        HashSet<Character>set=new HashSet<>();
        int count=0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            char ch=s.charAt(i);
            if(set.contains(ch)){
                count+=2;
                set.remove(ch);
            }else set.add(ch);
        }
        return set.size()==0?count:count+1;
    }
}
